TITLE: Toronto-area man jailed for counseling suicide, causing 2 deaths
SUMMARY: Kenneth Law, 57, of Mississauga, Ontario has been arrested for allegedly providing lethal substances to two people at risk of suicide.

TITLE: Mexican president accuses US of funding groups hostile to his administration, calls on Biden to intervene
SUMMARY: Mexico President Andres Manuel López Obrador is accusing the US Agency for International Development of funding organizations hostile to his administration.

TITLE: US spends nearly $300 million on military aid to Ukraine
SUMMARY: The United States has spent nearly $300 million in additional military aid to Ukraine. The new package will include Hydra-70 rockets, artillery rounds, howitzers and ammunition.

TITLE: Rwanda floods leave at least 129 dead
SUMMARY: Floods caused by torrential rainfall in northern and western Rwanda have left at least 129 people dead, according to a regional public broadcaster.

TITLE: Anticommunist dissident's shooting in Laos capital fuels investigation demand
SUMMARY: International human rights groups are calling for an investigation into the Saturday shooting of Lao activist and outspoken government critic Anousa Luangsuphom.

TITLE: Belgrade school shooting: boy kills 9 in planned attack
SUMMARY: The shooter, 13, who killed nine and injured six, is below Serbia's age of criminal responsibility — he will be placed in a psychiatric institution to serve his time.

TITLE: British tech chief warns AI's social impact 'as big as the Industrial Revolution,' urges national response
SUMMARY: Sir Patrick Vallance echoed the sentiments of fellow countryman and the "Godfather of AI" Geoffrey Hinton, who said he regretted creating the breakthrough that led to modern AI.

TITLE: Aid officials say Syria conditions dire, months after deadly quake
SUMMARY: Aid officials said that three months after the massive Feb. 6 earthquake hit Turkey and Syria the living conditions remained dire in Syria’s rebel-held northwest.

TITLE: US military carries out Syria drone strike targeting senior al-Qaida leader
SUMMARY: The U.S. military carried out a drone strike that targeted a senior al-Qaida leader in Syria. The strike hit a chicken farm near the town of Harem, which killed one person.

TITLE: Turkey closes airspace to Armenian flights over objections to monument
SUMMARY: Turkey's foreign minister announced his country closed its airspace to Armenian aircraft, in retaliation for the erection of a monument in the Armenian capital, Yerevan.

TITLE: Swedes pass anti-terror legislation, likely to help NATO membership bid
SUMMARY: Sweden passed anti-terror legislation that targets funding and assisting terrorist groups and joining terrorist group by travelling abroad. It is expected to aid the nation's NATO membership bid.

TITLE: 258 million people faced acute food insecurity in 2020, UN reports
SUMMARY: More than a quarter-billion people faced acute food insecurity during the pandemic, according to a United Nations report. The worst-off countries include Afghanistan, Yemen, and Haiti.

TITLE: Knife attack at Berlin school seriously injures 2 young girls
SUMMARY: A 39-year-old suspect allegedly attacked students at a school in Berlin, Germany. Two young girls, ages 7 and 8, sustained serious injuries.

TITLE: Gas leak at German high school exposes at least 84 to suspected irritant gas
SUMMARY: Both students and teachers at a German high school were exposed to an irritant gas. Three students and a teacher were taken to a hospital following the gas leak.

TITLE: Russia reducing Victory Day celebrations in wake of Ukraine war losses, drone attacks
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin has previously used the Victory Day celebrations as a moment to push his propaganda, including a rallying cry to "denazify" Ukraine in 2021.

TITLE: Brazil's federal police search home of former President Bolsonaro over alleged doctored vaccine cards
SUMMARY: Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro had his home searched and phone seized by Brazil's Federal Police Wednesday in an investigation into alleged doctored vaccine cards.

TITLE: 9 killed in explosion at Chinese petrochemical plant, 3 others dead in helicopter crash
SUMMARY: Three people died in a helicopter crash in China. At least nine others were killed in an explosion at a petrochemical plant during the country's May Day celebrations.

TITLE: Missing Madeleine McCann's parents 'await a breakthrough' in toddler's kidnapping
SUMMARY: Kate and Gerry McCann, the parents of missing British girl Madeleine McCann, said they "await a breakthrough" in a Tuesday statement marking 16 years since their daughter disappeared.

TITLE: Flooding in Italy leaves at least 2 dead
SUMMARY: Nonstop flooding in Italy left at least two people dead in the populous Emilia-Romagna region. One of the people who died was swept away by flood waters while riding a bike.

TITLE: Pope Francis greets Russian Orthodox leader amid secret Vatican 'mission' to end war in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Pope Francis met with Chairman for External Church Relations of the Moscow Patriarchate Anthony of Volokolamsk at the Vatican on Wednesday, speaking to one another at the pontiff's general audience.

TITLE: Police across Europe crackdown on Italian mob with raids, arrests
SUMMARY: Police are cracking down on Italy’s ’ndrangheta organized crime syndicate. Homes have been raided and millions of euros have been seized across Europe.

TITLE: Dissident Belarusian journalist who was pulled off of commercial flight sentenced to 8 years in prison
SUMMARY: Raman Pratasevich, a dissident journalist who was arrested after being pulled off a commercial flight, has been sentenced to eight years in prison.

TITLE: European Union announces plans to ramp up production of ammunition to help Ukraine
SUMMARY: Ukraine has been burning through ammunition at a furious rate. The EU announced they are planning to ramp up the production of ammunition to help Ukraine.

TITLE: Ukraine's President Volodymyr Zelenskyy asks for more firepower for his country during trip to Finland
SUMMARY: Volodymyr Zelenskyy, the president of Ukraine, visited Helsinki, Finland, today as part of an effort to secure firepower for his country's war with Russia.

TITLE: Russia claims Putin targeted in drone assassination attempt, as videos circulate online
SUMMARY: The Russian government claims two drones attempted to assassinate President Vladimir Putin at his residence within the Kremlin before being disabled by defense systems.
